Russian Equity Movers: Raspadskaya, Rosneft, Magnitogorsk Gain

-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 
2011-05-27T15:16:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/russian-equity-movers-raspadskaya-rosneft-magnitogorsk-gain.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  rose for the
first week in five, climbing 2 percent to 1,638.06 by the 6:45
p.m. close in Moscow, taking its advance in the week to 2.1
percent. The dollar-denominated RTS Index added 2.2 percent to
1,858.39.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Raspadskaya (RASP RX), a producer of coal for
steelmaking, surged 4 percent to 170.08 rubles, the highest
closing price since May 6, after RBC Daily reported that Russian
billionaire Gennady Timchenko is in talks to buy a controlling
stake in the company from Evraz Group SA, citing people it
didn’t identify.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX),  Russia ’s biggest oil producer, added
4.1 percent to 240.93 rubles, the strongest close since April
29, as crude gained as much as 1 percent to $101.24 a barrel on
speculation the global economic recovery will bolster demand for
energy.  OAO Severstal (CHMF RX), the nation’s largest steelmaker,
increased 3.9 percent to 506 rubles. OAO Magnitogorsk Iron &
Steel (MAGN RX) rose 4.2 percent, to 25.945 rubles. Copper, lead
and nickel led gains on the London Metal Exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Kay in London at 
